news.title: Gurugram civic body's takeover of two private colonies delayed again
news.para: ​The Mayfield Garden representative, however, raised objections over “inflated” estimates of the deficient infrastructure as the Greenwood City representative conveyed plans to plug the deficiencies before the handover.

news.title: Sebi to auction properties of Royal Twinkle, Citrus Check Inns on July 15
news.para: The properties to go under the hammer include office premises, residential flats, land parcel, shops, land & buildings located in Gujarat, Maharashtra, Goa, Daman, and Dadra and Nagar Haveli.

news.title: DLF to invest Rs 200 crore for expanding Delhi's Vasant Kunj mall
news.para: On an average, rentals for properties housing luxury brands are nearly double compared with mass-priced lifestyle brands. DLF is looking to more than double its retail portfolio and add about 5 million sq ft in the next 5-6 years with an investment of about ₹3,000 crore, the executive said.

news.title: TARC to demolish central Delhi mall for residential project, invest Rs 700 crore
news.para: "We have land parcels at some of the most prime locations of Delhi and Gurgaon, and this year, we plan to launch at least 5 projects. We will have two projects in Kapashera near the Delhi airport, one in Kirti Nagar in Central Delhi, one in sector 63 Gurgaon and another one in Hauz Khas," Sarin said.

news.title: Kesoram aims 15MT cement capacity, Rs 350-500 crore capex in 3-4 years
news.para: "We have decided to ramp up the cement capacity to 15 million tonnes in phases from 10-11 million tonnes now in the next 3-4 years. The total capex will be between Rs 350 and Rs 500 crore," Kesoram's whole-time director & CEO P Radhakrishnan said.

news.title: Mumbai: Omkar Group's promoter to return to jail on March 18
news.para: Justice Dangre accepted Ponda’s statement and said Varma’s interim application for medical bail thus stands disposed of.

news.title: DDA conducts second phase of draw for allotment of flats under In situ rehabilitation scheme
news.para: DDA has constructed 3,024 flats for the residents of Bhoomiheen Camp at Kalkaji Extension area under the scheme, and the first phase of the draw was conducted in February this year, they said.

news.title: Brick kilns across Punjab may soon use stubble pellets as fuel
news.para: Amid the rising prices as well as shortage of coal, the use of pellets would not only economically benefit the brick kiln owners but also the farmers, besides curbing the pollution.

news.title: BHIVE Workspace opens three lakh sq ft co-working space in Bengaluru
news.para: The addition of the new space takes the total footprint of the company to over nine lakh sq ft with over 22,000 seats across 17 hubs in Bengaluru.

news.title: RLDA invites bid for commercial development of land in Bengaluru for Rs 236 crore
news.para: “The land parcel is ideal for residential/ commercial development and is in the heart of the city. Its development shall boost the already developed economy of Bangalore and will provide well-developed residential apartments / commercial complexes to Bangalore city,” said Ved Parkash Dudeja, Vice Chairman, RLDA.

news.title: CIDCO gets SBI's Rs 5,000-crore line of credit for PMAY mega housing scheme
news.para: This financing is expected to help in speeding up the ongoing project with more than 1.12 lakh houses. The rate of interest for this financing is 6%, which is the lowest for any public sector undertaking for a line of credit of this size.

news.title: Nagpur: NIT fixes premium for commercial use of industrial plots higher than state
news.para: Its board of trustees on Thursday decided that a premium of 50% of ready reckoner value will have to be paid by an applicant for conversion of usage on industrial plot measuring over 4,001 sqft.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body conducts draw of flats under Atal Apartment scheme
news.para: The draw was conducted for 336 high income group (HIG) and 240 middle income group (MIG) flats. The LIT received 821 applications for HIG flats and 151 applications for 240 MIG flats.

news.title: Allahabad HC directs 20-day status quo on buildings in flood zone in Gautam Budh Nagar
news.para: Disposing the writ petition, a division bench comprising Justice Manoj Kumar Gupta and Justice Sameer Jain permitted the petitioner-society and its members to file objection within 10 days in pursuance of the public notice dated June 8.

news.title: Chennai: Land pooling pilot in Madambakkam
news.para: “We are in discussion with landowners whose plots fall in the Madambakkam pilot scheme and are trying to make the scheme successful through stakeholders’ participation and involvement,” Anshul Mishra, member secretary, CMDA said.
